url_description: Many people have already asked us ‚Äúwho are these R.A.M. guys actually?‚Äù So here is the short story. Whenever we think of patriotic or nationalist organizations in USA what pops up in your mind first ? The white cloaks of the KKK? Or Derek Vinyard from American History X - a canonic skinhead who is, despite the cool tattoo, a real dinosaur for us? Or maybe you think of all those weird geeks - 4chan trolls, who bombard the Internet with Pepe-memes ? R.A.M. Rise Above Movement - a group of friends from sunny California who were just working out together, but became an international fenomen in a patriotic movement! Read their full story in our channel - link in bio.

cleaned_message: Next, we went to Ukraine and met the organizer of WhiteRex Dennis who gave us a chance to compete again in Kyiv. Although we lost in the ring, it was still a victory in the sense that we were the first Americans to help bridge the two scenes. Shortly after our arrival back in the united states, the media put us in their sites. Two documentaries were put out on us that aired on national television. The media cried for police or arrests, even though we clearly defending ourselves against higher numbers and armed Antifa. But with enough media lies, they were finally able to get the FBI to brush the dust of the law book and find something - a law that hasn't been used in 70 years (!) to get after us. One night our home was raided by counter-terrorist task force and the FBI. Every window was destroyed in my apartment, and everything I owned was lost. Four of us were arrested that night for going to the ‚ÄûUnite the Right‚Äú rally in Charlottesville. Shortly after, I and three others were arrested for the fight in Huntington beach. The FBI went on national television claiming we were ‚Äûthe most violent white supremacist gang‚Äú and so on. To this day, not a single injury, victim or weapon has been found. Rise Above Movement was never about creating a massive organization but showing others a better, more positive way in the nationalist lifestyle. We wanted to just spread our ideals throughout America, but today we get emails and messages from all over telling us how much they changed their life around because of finding our videos. None of us that day in Huntington Beach could have ever predicted what would come next, but we would like to think we made a positive impact on our movement, making this all worthwhile.

The saying goes "dream big start small," but when eight friends that worked out together on the weekend decided to attend a Trump rally, hoping to land a few more like-minded patriots to their athletic club, things escalated very fast. On that day in Huntington Beach, California, Antifa showed up to shut down the Trump rally, as they have been doing in the previous months with success. Fights quickly broke out with Antifa sending a 60-year-old flag-waving woman to the ground. We all stepped in, and I saw the black-masked assailant who maced her and went after him, landing a few blows to the back of his head as he turned and fled, a second masked Antifa let of a stream of mace directly into my face from up close. With pure luck, I managed to take him to the ground and even land a few sloppy blows, before being pulled off and making my way into the ocean to relive my burning eyes and face. More clashes broke out and ended with us triumphantly chasing all the antifa off the beach and onto the streets. We all left and got lunch, and although there was some action, it was nothing we thought was too crazy or significant. Within a few hours, we realized we were wrong. Photos of us chasing Antifa began trending, and we began getting praise and hate from all sides. At the time, Trump was just elected, and any rally in support of him was met with left-wing violence, never before have nationalists fought back and got a clear victory as we did that day out right chasing them till police had to step in and protect them. At the same time, as all this tension because of Trump's presidency, the "Alt-Right" was growing in popularity. Although I agreed with its ideals, I didn't see a place in it for me. At the time, the alt-right was mostly guys in suits working on debate skills or many taking to the internet to troll and be edgy. Both these did seem to have the real-world presence i was looking for. So we set out on our taking inspiration from organizations such as Casapound and White Rex. With this newfound fame, we were able to put together a decent-sized crew and begin weekly trainings in MMA and boxing. We called it ‚ÄûRise Above Movement‚Äú and quickly added all forms of street activism to get more guys involved and spread our message. The idea was to be the real world change you want to see, in a world on consumerism, apathy and other left-wing ideas, we wanted to rise above that, get healthy and stronger. Our sole mission was to create a positive counter-culture to the left. So we pushed a strict no drug policy, encouraged guys to take up the healthy nationalist lifestyle we were pioneering in America, putting out videos to show our message in practice, not just in theory. Another event took place a few months later in the left-wing stronghold of Berekely, California. This time we were heavily outnumbered, Antifa came with weapons as police searched nationalist that entered the event taking flag poles and whatever else. M80 fireworks began to rain down on our side, and the police quickly went back to their patrol cars for donut breaks when the smell of violence took to the air. They hoped that we would be smashed by the mass of black block Antifa and send us home. Instead, within minutes a now well-trained crew of about ten of us jumped over the barrier the moment Antifa began beating a lone man. Quickly our training paid off as the rich college kids from Berkeley realized they weren't just facing boomers. It was a glorious day, a humiliating defeat to the left like never seen before in the streets of America! Since then, many saw that we brought a real-world change in a positive way, more than just trying to be edgy but instead defend and uplift fellow white brothers. RAM continued to grow and spread the idea of the healthy nationalist lifestyle in America. Eventually, we caught the eye of some of our European counterparts and were invited to compete in the tournament put on by KDN. We accepted and flew out, being the first Americans to compete and bring back a trophy.

March of the Defenders of Europe: 1920-2020 On 15 August 2020, Polish nationalists marched through Warsaw to celebrate the 100th anniversary of the victory in the Battle of Warsaw during the Polish-Soviet War. It was one of the most important battles in world history. The Polish army, which was on the verge of defeat in the summer of 1920, counterattacked and defeated the Red Army, inflicting huge losses and effectively stopping the planned expansion of Communism and Bolshevik terror into Western Europe. The heroism of Polish soldiers defending their homeland despite all the odds, the brilliant command of Marshall J√≥zef Pi≈Çsudski and General Tadeusz Rozwadowski, and the breaking of Soviet ciphers by Polish cryptologists all contributed to this victory. The memory of this battle is important for us nationalists, reminding us of the sacrifice of our ancestors and remaining an inspiration for the young generation fighting for free Poland and free Europe of Nations against new, even more destructive forms of Bolshevism and globalism. The march was organized by Young Europe and Nationalist Warsaw. Members of several Polish radical nationalist organizations gathered, including ONR (National Radical Camp), NOP (National Rebirth of Poland), representatives of the National-Radical magazine "Szturm!", Association for Culture and Tradition "Niklot", Autonomous Nationalists, as well as our Czech friends from NSF - N√°rodn√≠ a soci√°ln√≠ fronta. The march started near the monument of Wincenty Witos, with a little delay due to a discussion with city officials who tried, in a shameful and legally questionable way, to prevent participants from presenting the symbols of nationalism and of the Pagan tradition of our ancestors, proceeded through the Royal Route in Warsaw's historical centre and ended at the monument of J√≥zef Pi≈Çsudski, the supreme commander of Polish army in 1920. The main banner of the march read "Polish Victory - Freedom for Europe", emphasizing the pan-European dimension of the struggle. Another banner, belonging to the nationalist circle of Young Europe, read "It will be an empire, if it arises from our blood" - an inspiring quote from the poet Andrzej Trzebi≈Ñski. url_title: Uncover The Truth Behind "Patient Zero" (AIDS)
url_description: The story of the AIDS epidemic and the man accused of starting it. When a new, deadly virus spreads across North America at an alarming rate, one man is singled out for bringing the disease to the continent. Spanning the 1970s until today, the story of Gaetan Dugas ‚Äìaka ‚ÄòPatient Zero‚Äô ‚Äìserves as the perfect microcosm of the evolution of AIDS in America and the country‚Äôs response to it. In the early 1980s, little was known about this global epidemic, except that it seemed to be most prevalent amongst gay men. America was in the grip of fear and uncertainty and, in the scramble for answers, Dugas would become known and vilified as ‚ÄòPatient Zero‚Äô. Exploring timely themes about fear, the demonizing of the unknown, and the danger of false narratives, this FadooProductions and Fine Point Films documentary weaves social history and scientific investigation into a poignant story of an individual who became intrinsically and tragically linked with AIDS.
